flowRoot.flowPara: Figure S10. List of genes that are ancestrally essential in at least one sub-clade of the Enterobacteriaceae family in this study and their essentiality status in all sub-clades. Black indicates that the gene is ancestrally essential in that sub-clade and white indicates that the gene is not ancestrally essential. Genes that are essential using Fitch's algorithm in a sub-clade are considered core essential in that sub-clade.
